                  <interp inst="t17690405-16-crimeloc90" type="placeName" value="Enfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17690405-16-crimeloc90" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17690405-16-off88 t17690405-16-crimeloc90"></join>. On Monday the 27th of Feb. I mist 40 s. worth of halfpence out of my compting house. I had a suspicion of the prisoner. I followed him and searched him; I found eleven shillings in halfpence upon him. He confessed he had hid the rest in a bag in a dunghill, and went with me to shew me, where I found them.</p>
               <p>Q. Was the prisoner your servant?</p>
               <p>Brough. He had been my <rs id="t17690405-16-deflabel91" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17690405-16-defend148 t17690405-16-deflabel91"></join>, but was gone away.</p>
               <p>Q. How old is he?</p>
               <p>Brough. He is about fourteen years old. His father has worked at my house thirty years. I should be glad to recommend him to mercy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17690405-16-person152">
                  Thomas 
                  Oliver 
